text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!SignLanguage]]%0a%0a!Similarities and differences between signed languages%0a%0a:Author: BrandonW%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aLooking at similarities and differences between ASL and BSL%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aSigned languages are created not based on a country's spoken language, but based on proximity to and interaction with others using sign language. Hence, there are differences between American Sign Language (ASL) and British Sign Language (BSL). It is so different that a person using ASL would not be able to understand a person using BSL and vice versa. %0a%0aOne difference is that ASL users use only one hand for the alphabet while BSL users use both hands for the alphabet. Another difference is that ASL users use fingerspelling, which is spelling words that don't have an designated sign, much more often than BSL users, who more often create signs that would be eventually use more widespread. Signs for some words can be done differently in ASL and BSL. For the word "deaf", both ASL and BSL users touch their ear and then their mouth. But, people using ASL only use their index finger while people using BSL use both their index and middle finger, which are touching together.%0a%0aSimilarities are that there are many regional dialects/accents within the ASL and BSL communities. As well, people using sign language abide to internationally accepted signs when different sign languages users come together in international meetings. There is a significant overlap in vocabulary and signs. Core features of sign languages can be found in ASL and BSL such as topic-comment syntax, which is when the topic is communicated first and then the comment about the topic is next.%0a%0aSources: https://takelessons.com/blog/2021/01/whats-the-difference-between-asl-bsl#:~:text=Just%2520like%2520ASL%252C%2520British%2520Sign,used%2520by%2520the%2520Deaf%2520community.&text=As%2520with%2520ASL%252C%2520BSL%2520also,and%2520New%2520Zealand%2520Sign%2520Language.%0ahttps://www.quora.com/What-are-some-interesting-differences-between-American-Sign-Language-and-British-Sign-Language%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: C:)%0a(:Category: SignLanguage:)
